genresAdvancedInfo.name: czech classical piano
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Czech classical piano music is a subgenre of Czech classical music that focuses on piano compositions by Czech composers. This music is known for its technical virtuosity and emotional depth, and it often incorporates elements of Czech folk music.
